# PROJECT CONTEXT — loaded once, referenced always

## Project Name
TraceLink

## What This Project Does
Privacy-compliant link tracking and fingerprinting tool that logs visits, enriches them with IP/location/ASN data, and exposes them via an API and Netlify function for use in bots or other clients.

## Tech Stack
- Frontend: Vanilla JS with HTML/CSS in `public`
- Backend: Node.js with Express, Netlify Functions, and Serverless HTTP
- Database: PostgreSQL via Prisma ORM
- AI/LLM: None currently
- Hosting: Netlify
- Other: Telegram Bot via Telegraf, Redis for caching/rate limiting, Prisma for database access

## Key Files & What They Do
- `src/index.js` — main Express application entrypoint
- `netlify/functions/api.js` — serverless handler wrapping the Express app for Netlify
- `prisma/schema.prisma` — database schema and Prisma configuration

## Current State
Core Express server, Netlify serverless entrypoint, and Prisma schema are in place; overall feature completeness and production readiness are unknown from the current snapshot.

## Rules For This Project
- Never touch `prisma/migrations` unless explicitly told to
- Always use existing Express and Prisma patterns already in use when adding new endpoints or models
- All new code must follow the existing camelCase naming convention for JavaScript functions and variables
- Do not install new packages without flagging it first
